{
  "text": "In the HV environment, the private shock was drawn from a uniform distribution on the interval [\u221224, 24] . In the LV environment, the private shock was drawn from [CITATION_1] . The variance of the common shock was kept constant in both environments and was drawn from a uniform distribution on the interval [\u221227, 27]. The cost parameter was fixed at c = 110, the outside option was held constant for all environments and con- [CITATION_2] Recall that HV means that the variance of the private shock was high relative to the common shock, whereas LV variance treatment means that variance of the private shock was low relative to the common shock.",
